SIMPLE: provoke
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Provoke
<hw>Pro*voke"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Provoked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Provoking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>provoquer</ets>, L. <ets>provocare</ets> to call forth;
<ets>pro</ets> forth + <ets>vocare</ets> to call, fr. <ets>vox</ets>,
<ets>vocis</ets>, voice, cry, call. See <er>Voice</er>.]</ety> <def>To
call forth; to call into being or action; esp., to incense to action, a
faculty or passion, as love, hate, or ambition; hence, commonly, to
incite, as a person, to action by a challenge, by taunts, or by
defiance; to exasperate; to irritate; to offend intolerably; to cause to
retaliate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Obey his voice, <qex>provoke</qex> him not.</q> <rj><qau>Ex.
xxiii. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye fathers, <qex>provoke</qex> not your children to wrath.</q>
<rj><qau>Eph. vi. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such acts⟦br⟧
Of contumacy will <qex>provoke</qex> the Highest⟦br⟧
To make death in us live.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Can honor's voice <qex>provoke</qex> the silent dust?</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the poet the meaning is what he pleases to make it, what it
<qex>provokes</qex> in his own soul.</q> <rj><qau> J.
Burroughs.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To irritate; arouse; stir up; awake; excite;
incite; anger. See <er>Irritate</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provoke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Provoke
<hw>Pro*voke"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cause
provocation or anger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To appeal. <note>[A Latinism]</note></def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provokement</ent>⟦br⟧
